        <h2 class="bridge-h">Attestrack gets<br />you tracking right.<br /><em>Attestrue proves it.</em></h2>
        <p class="bridge-p">Attestrack solves the signal quality problem — better data, no middlemen, your infrastructure. If you ever receive a CIPA demand letter, the question shifts from "did consent happen" to "can you prove it happened correctly, independently, at the moment it occurred."</p>
        <p class="bridge-p">Because you're already running Attestrack, the upgrade to Attestrue independent proof is one environment variable. No new infrastructure. No migration. The consent records you've been accumulating in shadow mode become signed, independently witnessed records the moment you add a license key. The trust chain follows the Consent Evidence Trust Chain (CETS): RFC 8785-shaped records, stable <code>record_id</code>, Ed25519 witness signatures, dual proof anchors, and a <code>daily_root</code> over sorted record IDs for batch verification—not a bespoke Merkle product path.</p>
        <p class="bridge-p"><strong>You don't need to think about this today.</strong> Attestrack runs for free as long as you want. When the question becomes legal rather than technical, the answer is already deployed.</p>
        <ul class="bridge-path">
          <li class="bp-item"><div class="bp-n">Now</div><div class="bp-body">Deploy Attestrack free. Better signal quality immediately. No legal infrastructure needed yet.</div></li>
          <li class="bp-item"><div class="bp-n">Later</div><div class="bp-body">Add <code>LICENSE_KEY = "&lt;your-license-key&gt;"</code> to <code>wrangler.toml</code>. Consent records become independently signed. Proof layer active.</div></li>
          <li class="bp-item"><div class="bp-n">When needed</div><div class="bp-body">Demand letter arrives. TIR and Corroboration Certificate generated from your existing signed records. Two independent records. Your defense is already built.</div></li>
        </ul>
